attributes.gcd: Refers to the date as on which the snapshot of source data extracted for processing.
Refers to the correlation coefficient value between different Units of Measure. The value stored should be in the range of -1 to +1.

Refers to the correlation method used to arrive at the correlation coefficient value. These methods can be Pearson's R, Spearman's Rho, Kendall's Tau. List of values of this column is referred from DIM_DISTRIBUTION_FITTING_TYPE.V_DISTR_FITTING_TYPE_CODE.
Refers to the column that stores the Matrix type which is generally the Correlation Matrix.

Refers to the source system from where data is extracted. Data can be sourced from multiple sources, this column will Refers to the source code from where the data is extracted for this extraction date.
Refers to the record creation date. It has been added to all catalog entities to enable partitioning and archival.
Refers to the run identifier for a set of Records participating in the particular Run with the Run Execution identifier. This is a combination of Run Main Identifier and Run Execution Identifier.

Refers to the unique code for Unit of Measure defined through AMHM.   List of values of this column is referred from DIM_UOM_B.V_UOM_CODE.  UOM  is the granularity at which frequency & severity modelling happens.  UOM Mapping can be defined at granularity of Line of Business, Event Type, risk category, etc. . Combination of member of these source hierarchies are assigned to unique Unit of Measure code.
